    {
      "id": "exec-summary",
      "layout": "CONTENT_FULL",
      "section": "Executive Summary",
      "sectionIndex": 1,
      "content": {
        "title": "Executive Summary",
        "body": "Belantamab mafodotin (BLENREP®) is a first-in-class anti-BCMA antibody-drug conjugate (ADC) approved for the treatment of relapsed/refractory multiple myeloma (RRMM). In Germany, approximately 7,000 new cases of multiple myeloma are diagnosed annually, with a significant unmet medical need in patients who have received ≥3 prior lines of therapy.\n\nThe DREAMM clinical program has demonstrated compelling efficacy across multiple combination regimens. DREAMM-7 showed a median PFS of 36.6 months for BVd vs 13.4 months for DVd (HR 0.41, p<0.001). DREAMM-8 demonstrated BPd superiority over Pd with an ORR of 77% vs 55%.\n\nThe 2027 Medical Affairs strategy focuses on three strategic imperatives: (1) Establishing BVd as the preferred 2L+ regimen through medical education and KOL engagement, (2) Generating real-world evidence to support G-BA HTA submission, and (3) Expanding the BCMA-ADC narrative through combination data and ISR programs.",
        "references": [
          {"id": "ref-1", "text": "Dimopoulos MA et al. NEJM 2024;391:1–12", "tier": 1, "type": "pubmed"},
          {"id": "ref-2", "text": "Trudel S et al. Lancet 2024;403:1230–40", "tier": 1, "type": "pubmed"},
          {"id": "ref-3", "text": "Robert Koch Institut, Krebsregisterdaten 2024", "tier": 2, "type": "guideline"}
        ]
      }
